trend_summary: From earliest to latest image, suburban blocks fill in, industrial strips along the southern highway thicken, and several new cul-de-sac clusters emerge. Road widening and a fresh interchange improve north–south connectivity. Tree cover remains high, preserving golf course and riparian corridors, so growth is mainly infill rather than sprawl.
notable_changes: Expansion of industrial/commercial roofs along the south-edge highway corridor.
New residential cul-de-sac pockets added in central and northeastern sectors.
North–south arterial widened and given a new interchange loop.
Slight densification of town center: larger white-roofed retail/office blocks replace small lots.
Mature tree canopy preserved; golf course and river greenway unchanged.
